Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: SUPPLEMENTAL RESTRAINT SYSTEMS: AIRBAG SYSTEM: B1627/82,B1628/82,B1637/82,B1638/82,B1647/82,B1648/82,B167B/82,B167C/82; Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor LH; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

DTC

B1627/82

Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor LH

DTC

B1628/82

Side Airbag Sensor Assembly LH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B1637/82

Lost Communication with Rear Airbag Sensor LH

DTC

B1638/82

Rear Airbag Sensor Assembly LH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B1647/82

Lost Communication with Side Satellite Sensor Bus LH

DTC

B1648/82

Side Satellite Sensor Bus LH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B167B/82

Lost Communication with Front Door Pressure Sensor LH

DTC

B167C/82

Front Door Pressure Sensor LH Initialization Incomplete

DESCRIPTION

The side collision sensor LH circuit consists of the airbag ECU assembly, door side airbag sensor LH, side airbag sensor assembly LH and rear airbag sensor LH.

The door side airbag sensor LH, side airbag sensor assembly LH and rear airbag sensor LH detect impacts to the vehicle and send signals to the airbag ECU assembly to determine if the airbags and pretensioners should be deployed.

These DTCs are stored when a malfunction is detected in the side collision sensor LH circuit.

DTC No.

Detection Item

DTC Detection Condition

Trouble Area

Test Mode / Check Mode

B1627/82

Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor LH

  • The airbag ECU assembly detects a line short, short to ground or B+, or an open in the side collision sensor LH circuit.
  • Side airbag sensor assembly LH malfunction
  • Rear airbag sensor LH malfunction
  • Door side airbag sensor LH malfunction
  • Airbag ECU assembly malfunction
  • Floor wire
  • Front door wire LH
  • Side airbag sensor assembly LH
  • Rear airbag sensor LH
  • Door side airbag sensor LH
  • Airbag ECU assembly

Does not apply to test/check mode

(a) Check for current DTCs.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Trouble Codes

HINT:

  • DTCs indicating communication errors will be changed to DTCs indicating errors in initialization by turning the power switch off and then on (IG) again.
  • Codes other than current DTCs B1627, B1628, B1637, B1638, B1647, B1648, B167B, B167C and 82 may be output at this time, but they are not related to this check.

A

2.

CHECK CONNECTORS

(a) Turn the power switch off.

(b) Disconnect the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

CAUTION:

Wait at least 90 seconds after disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal to disable the SRS system.

(c) Check that the connectors are properly connected to the airbag ECU assembly, side airbag sensor assembly LH, rear airbag sensor LH and door side airbag sensor LH. Also check that the connectors that link the floor wire and front door wire LH are properly connected.

OK:

The connectors are properly connected.

HINT:

If the connectors are not properly connected, reconnect the connectors and proceed to the next inspection.

(d) Disconnect the connectors from the airbag ECU assembly, side airbag sensor assembly LH, rear airbag sensor LH and door side airbag sensor LH. Also disconnect the connectors that link the floor wire and front door wire LH.

(e) Check that the terminals of the connectors are not deformed or damaged.

OK:

The terminals are not deformed or damaged.

15.

CHECK SIDE AIRBAG SENSOR ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Connect the connectors to the rear airbag sensor LH, door side airbag sensor LH and airbag ECU assembly.

*1

Side Airbag Sensor Assembly RH

*2

Airbag ECU Assembly

(b) Interchange the side airbag sensor assembly LH with RH and connect the connectors.

(c) Connect the cable to the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

(d) Clear the DTCs stored in memory.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Clear DTCs

(e) Turn the power switch off.

(f) Turn the power switch on (IG), and wait for at least 60 seconds.

(g) Check for DTCs.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Trouble Codes

HINT:

Codes other than DTCs B1642, B1643, B1647, B1648, 81 and 82 may be output at this time, but they are not related to this check.

Result

Proceed to

A

DTC B1642, B1643 or 81 is output.

B

C

(h) Turn the power switch off.

(i) Disconnect the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

CAUTION:

Wait at least 90 seconds after disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal to disable the SRS system.

(j) Return the side airbag sensor assembly LH and RH to their original positions and connect the connectors.
